"2GM":{"department":"PWR","number":"2GM","title":"Writing & Rhetoric 2:  Unpredictable Dialogue: Art of the Interview, Art of the Essay","description":"Prerequisite: PWR 1.  Further work in developing skills in argument and research-based writing, with emphasis on both written and oral/multimedia presentation of research. Study of the rhetorical craft of the interview, exploring structure, language, timing, and development in a range of forums, including documentaries, radio, transcription, campus conversations, and television. Research of a Stanford professor&iquest;s work, including interview.  Presentation of findings from research and interview to the class.  See http://www.stanford.edu/dept/undergrad/cgi-bin/drupal_ual/AP_univ_req_PWR_Courses.html.","min_units":4,"max_units":4,"gers":["Writing 2"],"id":210398,},
