"2KS":{"department":"PWR","number":"2KS","title":"Writing & Rhetoric 2:  Happy Now?   The Anatomy of Happiness","description":"Prerequisite: PWR 1.  Further work in developing skills in argument and research-based writing, with emphasis on both written and oral/multimedia presentation of research. How the emerging field of happiness studies involves psychologists, economists and policy-makers in defining what happiness is and determining how society might create the conditions in which it can flourish.  Exploration of how happiness studies can uncover happiness at the heart of arguments about democracy, religion, and personal lifestyles, exploring what makes people happy across cultural, social, and national contexts.  See http://www.stanford.edu/dept/undergrad/cgi-bin/drupal_ual/AP_univ_req_PWR_Courses.html.","min_units":4,"max_units":4,"gers":["Writing 2"],"id":210365,},
